Luminar in Debt-Swap Talks With RBS, Lloyds, Mail on Sunday Says

-- B y   E r i k   L a r s o n
-- 
2011-08-28T14:07:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/luminar-in-debt-swap-talks-with-rbs-lloyds-mail-on-sunday-says.html
Luminar Group Holdings Plc (LMR)  is in
talks to exchange its debt for equity, giving control of the the
U.K. nightclub operator to Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc,
 Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY)  and Barclays Plc, the Mail on Sunday
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Luminar also seeks a capital injection from a third-party
investor to cut its debt of 82 million pounds ($134.2 million)
and a tax liability of 45 million pounds, the newspaper
reported. A sale of the entire company is also being considered,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Larson in London at 
 elarson4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
